entries.meaning: A wrong, unsuitable, misleading, or injurious name or designation; misnomer.
examples: Like the name Macon Dead, it is a misname imposed by someone with no concern about the consequences.

verbs.description: misname (third-person singular simple present misnames, present participle misnaming, simple past and past participle misnamed)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To call by a wrong name.
(transitive) To give an unsuitable or injurious name to; name incorrectly.
